3.23	Gideon_Byamugisha	Gideon Byamugisha	As he started to travel and speak about his condition, Byamugisha began encountering other religious leaders who were HIV infected, or personally affected by the death and illness of family members, but were not ready to publicly discuss their conditions. At the time, there was much misinformation about AIDS and HIV in Africa, and because of the promises and edicts from Christian, Muslim and Hindu groups on the continent, to have a religious leader infected or even affected personally was unthinkable.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/cd/Anerela_organization_logo.jpg/220px-Anerela_organization_logo.jpg
